table_markdown:
| KEY             | Description                                                  |
|------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------|
| Array            | A collection of elements identified by index or key, allowing easy access to each item. |
| Linked List      | A linear data structure where each element is a separate object, linked using pointers. |
| Stack            | A collection of elements that follows the Last In First Out (LIFO) principle. |
| Queue            | A collection of elements that follows the First In First Out (FIFO) principle. |
| Hash Table       | A data structure that stores key-value pairs for efficient data retrieval based on keys. |
| Tree             | A hierarchical data structure consisting of nodes, where each node has a value and links to child nodes. |
| Graph            | A collection of nodes (vertices) connected by edges, used to represent relationships or connections. |
| Set              | An unordered collection of unique elements, often used to perform mathematical set operations. |
